Anglesey's Ysgol Goronwy Owen appoints governors
Six new governors have been appointed to a troubled Anglesey school.It follows an inquiry into complaints from five teachers at Ysgol Goronwy Owen in Benllech that they could no longer work with the head teacher.Ann Hughes is currently suspended on full pay pending a decision from that investigation.According to Anglesey council's education department, they will be in a position to make a statement once the process has been fully completed.Three temporary head teachers have been in charge in the interim.The disruption has seen some parents take their children to other schools.